50|$|The bead test is a {{traditional}} part of qualitative inorganic analysis to test {{for the presence of}} certain metals. The oldest one is the <b>borax</b> <b>bead</b> test or blister test. It was introduced by Berzelius in 1812. Since then other salts were used as fluxing agents, such as sodium carbonate or sodium fluoride. The most important one after borax is microcosmic salt, which is the basis of the microcosmic salt bead test.|$|E

